svg.text: Image showing deprivation profiles of local authorities in Scotland. To create the shapes, data zones in Scotland
were ranked using the Scottish Index of Multiple Deprivation measure, and were divided into twenty buckets
(vigintiles). The distribution of data zones in each local authority was plotted, with more deprived data zones at the
bottom of the plots, and less deprived data zones at the top. To interpret the shapes - a larger bottom indicates
more deprived data zones in the area, while a larger top indicates fewer deprived data zones.
Data: Scottish Index of Multiple Deprivation |https://statistics.gov.scot/data/scottish-index-of-multi
Visualisation created in R Studio and Adobe Illustrator by Jamie Whyte and Julian Tait of Open Data Manchester
